reviews.review_text:
Grateful Dead Live at RFK Stadium on 1973-06-09 Notes are right, it was murderously hot that day, and precious little shade. I actually got dizzy and half-collapsed under the grandstand during the early part of the set, recovering in time to stagger back out for "Box of Rain." Spent the rest of the day back under the overhang. Allmans were fantastic.

Two years later, I briefly met Garcia at a club in Fairfax, Calif., and mentioned this show. He immediately apologized for what he called a "horrible" performance, and expressed genuine regret that I hadn't been there the following night.
Great PITB Jerry has some screw-ups here and there.  But he is smokin' in PITB!

memories one of my memories of this show was being 50 feet from the stage and the HEAT. There was a girl in front of us who weighed in at about 80 pounds drinking a bottle of SoCo. She was out of it, and after every  Dead song would stand up and holler for " Whipping Post" . She passed out before the Allmans hit the stage and slept through their entire show.

GD/RFK i was there for this show. was near 100 degrees and one of the Bros amps caught on fire and was pushed off the stage and replaced in no time. i was sitting up front and got some great pics of Garcia and the Bros.
